The paper describes a set of text analysis tools that can help analysts explore large document collections quickly. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions several natural language processing tasks such as named entity recognition and term extraction, which are commonly studied in the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a database to store meta-information, which suggests that it may be relevant to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. The paper's focus on automatic analysis and annotation of text suggests that it may also be relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper's mention of a zoomable and hyperlinked geographic map suggests that it may be relevant to the Digital Libraries (cs.DL) sub-category.
